### 1. Add a Student (POST)
# Run this a few times, changing the student_id (1-10) and score (0-100) to populate the mock DB.
POST http://localhost:5000/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Isaac",
  "middle_name": "G",
  "last_name": "Smith",
  "student_id": 1,
  "score": 85.5
}

### 2. Add Another Student (POST)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Alice",
  "middle_name": "",
  "last_name": "Johnson",
  "student_id": 2,
  "score": 92.0
}

### 3. Get Sorted Students (GET)
# This will return the list sorted from lowest to highest score.
GET http://localhost:5000/api/students

### 4. Get the Class Average (GET)
# This calculates the mathematical average of the inputs.
GET http://localhost:5000/api/average